file.name: ramp_openapi_with_extensions.yml
file.content:
servers:
  - url: 'https://rampdb.nih.gov'
 # - url: 'https://ramp-api-alpha.ncats.io'
  # - url: 'http://127.0.0.1:5762/'
openapi: 3.0.3
info:
  description: Relational Database of Metabolic Pathways (RaMP) API
  title: RaMP API v1.0.1
  version: 1.0.1
  contact:
    name: RaMP
    x-role: responsible developer
    email: NCATSRaMP@nih.gov
    x-id: 'https://github.com/tsheils'
  termsOfService: https://rampdb.nih.gov
tags:
  - name: NCATS-API
paths:
  /api/source_versions:
    get:
      summary: Return source version information
      responses:
        '200':
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
        '500':
          description: Internal Server Error
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: string
        default:
          description: Default response.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
      parameters: []
  /api/id-types:
    get:
      summary: Return analyte ID types
      responses:
        '200':
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
        '500':
          description: Internal Server Error
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: string
        default:
          description: Default response.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
      parameters: []
  /api/entity_counts:
    get:
      summary: Return counts on entities and their associations
      responses:
        '200':
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
        '500':
          description: Internal Server Error
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: string
        default:
          description: Default response.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
      parameters: []
  /api/analyte_intersects:
    get:
      summary: Return analyte source intersects
      responses:
        '200':
          description: OK
        '500':
          description: Internal Server Error
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: string
        default:
          description: Default response.
      parameters:
        - name: analytetype
          description: >-
            specifies type of analyte intersects to return, 'metabolites' or
            'genes'
          in: query
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - name: query_scope
          description: specifies 'global' or 'mapped-to-pathway'
          in: query
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
          example:
            analytetype: "metabolites"
            query_scope: "mapped-to-pathway"
  /api/ontology-types:
    get:
      summary: Return all types of ontologies present in RaMP-DB
      responses:
        '200':
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
        '500':
          description: Internal Server Error
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: string
        default:
          description: Default response.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
      parameters: []
  /api/chemical-class-type:
    get:
      summary: Return available high level chemical class types (from ClassyFire)
      responses:
        '200':
          description: OK
        '500':
          description: Internal Server Error
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: string
        default:
          description: Default response.
      parameters:
        - name: classtype
          in: query
          required: false
          schema:
            type: string
  /api/pathways-from-analytes:
    post:
      summary: Return pathways from given list of analytes
      responses:
        '200':
          description: OK
        '500':
          description: Internal Server Error
      requestBody:
        description: Retrieve pathway(s) for a given analyte(s). IDs should be prepended by ID source (e.g. **hmdb**:C00412).
        required: true
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              type: object
              properties:
                analytes:
                  type: array
                  items:
                    type: string
              example: # Sample object
                analytes: ["ensembl:ENSG00000135679", "hmdb:HMDB0000064", "hmdb:HMDB0000148", "ensembl:ENSG00000141510"]
  /api/analytes-from-pathways:
    post:
      summary: Retrieve analytes (genes/proteins, metabolites) by pathway.
      responses:
        '200':
          description: OK
        '500':
          description: Internal Server Error
      requestBody:
        description: Enter exact pathway name(s). `analyte_type` should be `"gene"`, `"metabolite"`, or `"both"` *(default)*
        required: true
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              type: object
              properties:
                pathway:
                  type: array
                  items:
                    type: string
                analyte_type:
                  type: string
                  enum: ["gene", "metabolite", "both"]
                  required: false
              example:
                pathway: [ "De Novo Triacylglycerol Biosynthesis", "sphingolipid metabolism"]
                analyte_type: "both"
  /api/ontologies-from-metabolites:
    post:
      summary: Return ontologies from list of metabolites
      responses:
        '200':
          description: OK
        '500':
          description: Internal Server Error
      requestBody:
        description: Enter a list of metabolites. IDs should be prepended by ID source (e.g. **kegg**:C00412).
        required: true
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              type: object
              properties:
                metabolite:
                  type: array
                  items:
                    type: string
                NameOrIds:
                  type: string
                  enum: [ "name", "ids"]
                  required: false
              example:
                metabolite: [ "ensembl:ENSG00000135679", "hmdb:HMDB0000064", "hmdb:HMDB0000148", "ensembl:ENSG00000141510"]
                NameOrIds: "ids"
  /api/metabolites-from-ontologies:
    post:
      summary: Return metabolites from ontology
      responses:
        '200':
          description: OK
        '500':
          description: Internal Server Error
      requestBody:
        description: Enter ontology(ies) and retrieve corresponding analytes (metabolites).
        required: true
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              type: object
              properties:
                ontology:
                  type: array
                  items:
                    type: string
                format:
                  type: string
                  enum: [ "json", "tsv" ]
                  required: false
              example:
                ontology: ["Colon", "Liver", "Lung"]
                format: "json"
  /api/chemical-classes:
    post:
      summary: Return available chemical classes of given metabolites in RaMP-DB
      responses:
        '200':
          description: OK
        '500':
          description: Internal Server Error
      requestBody:
        description: Retrieve chemical class information (from ClassyFire and LIPID MAPS) for input metabolite IDs. IDs should be prepended by ID source (e.g. **hmdb**:C00412).
        required: true
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              type: object
              properties:
                metabolites:
                  type: array
                  items:
                    type: string
                biospecimen:
                  type: string
                  enum: ["Blood", "Adipose", "Heart", "Urine", "Brain", "Liver", "Kidney", "Saliva", "Feces"]
                  required: false
              example:
                metabolites: ["hmdb:HMDB0000056", "hmdb:HMDB0000439", "hmdb:HMDB0000479", "hmdb:HMDB0000532",
                              "hmdb:HMDB0001015", "hmdb:HMDB0001138", "hmdb:HMDB0029159", "hmdb:HMDB0029412",
                              "hmdb:HMDB0034365", "hmdb:HMDB0035227", "hmdb:HMDB0007973", "hmdb:HMDB0008057",
                              "hmdb:HMDB0011211"]
  /api/chemical-properties:
    post:
      summary: Return chemical properties of given metabolites
      responses:
        '200':
          description: OK
        '500':
          description: Internal Server Error
      requestBody:
        description: Retrieve chemical properties (smiles, inchi_key, inchi_key_prefix, inchi, mw, monoisotop_mass, formula, common_name) from input metabolites. IDs should be prepended by ID source (e.g. **hmdb**:C00412).
        required: true
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              type: object
              properties:
                metabolites:
                  type: array
                  items:
                    type: string
              example:
                metabolites: [ "hmdb:HMDB0000056", "hmdb:HMDB0000439", "hmdb:HMDB0000479", "hmdb:HMDB0000532",
                               "hmdb:HMDB0001015", "hmdb:HMDB0001138", "hmdb:HMDB0029159", "hmdb:HMDB0029412",
                               "hmdb:HMDB0034365", "hmdb:HMDB0035227", "hmdb:HMDB0007973", "hmdb:HMDB0008057",
                               "hmdb:HMDB0011211" ]
  /api/common-reaction-analytes:
    post:
      summary: Return analytes involved in same reaction as given list of analytes
      responses:
        '200':
          description: OK
        '500':
          description: Internal Server Error
      requestBody:
        description: Retrieve Analytes Involved in the Same Reaction. IDs should be prepended by ID source (e.g. **hmdb**:C00412).
        required: true
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              type: object
              properties:
                analyte:
                  type: array
                  items:
                    type: string
                NameOrIds:
                  type: string
                  enum: [ "name", "ids" ]
                  required: false
              example:
                analyte: [ "ensembl:ENSG00000135679", "hmdb:HMDB0000064", "hmdb:HMDB0000148", "ensembl:ENSG00000141510"]
  /api/combined-fisher-test:
    post:
      summary: Return combined Fisher's test results from given list of analytes query results
      responses:
        '200':
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: object
        '500':
          description: Internal Server Error
      requestBody:
        description: Perform Pathway Enrichment. IDs should be prepended by ID source (e.g. **hmdb**:C00412). Input analyte IDs can be a mix of genes/proteins or metabolites.
        required: true
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              type: object
              properties:
                analytes:
                  type: array
                  items:
                    type: string
                biospecimen:
                  type: string
                  enum: [ "Blood", "Adipose", "Heart", "Urine", "Brain", "Liver", "Kidney", "Saliva", "Feces" ]
                  required: false
              example: # Sample object
                analytes: ["hmdb:HMDB0000033", "hmdb:HMDB0000052", "hmdb:HMDB0000094", "hmdb:HMDB0000161",
                           "hmdb:HMDB0000168", "hmdb:HMDB0000191", "hmdb:HMDB0000201", "chemspider:10026",
                           "hmdb:HMDB0006059", "Chemspider:6405", "CAS:5657-19-2", "hmdb:HMDB0002511",
                           "chemspider:20171375", "CAS:133-32-4", "CAS:5746-90-7", "CAS:477251-67-5", "hmdb:HMDB0000695",
                           "chebi:15934", "CAS:838-07-3", "hmdb:HMDBP00789", "hmdb:HMDBP00283", "hmdb:HMDBP00284",
                           "hmdb:HMDBP00850"]
  /api/filter-fisher-test-results:

            schema:
              type: object

                metabolites:

                  items:

                  type: string
                  enum: [ "Blood", "Adipose", "Heart", "Urine", "Brain", "Liver", "Kidney", "Saliva", "Feces" ]
